108806389328370273882<//userid>
<Name>Deanna Smith<//Name><Date>1612206163887< /Date><rate>5</rate>< Review>
I was very impressed with Dr. Lee and his staff.  They were very professional, efficient and friendly.  The office was very clean and they adhere to all safety precautions during the current Coronavirus pandemic which really helped put my mind at ease.

Though I live in the Valley, and the office is in Koreatown, I highly recommend Dr. Lee.  After doing extensive research, I went to Dr. Lee because I needed a qualified Endodontist and was not disappointed.  It is always hard to trust strictly based on Yelp or Google reviews since you never know who is writing them.  But Dr. Lee is by far the best Endodontist I have ever been to and is well worth the drive.  They even have Saturday appointments available which makes things very convenient if you work during the week.  In addition, they have a parking structure, at no charge, that provides ample parking and each level has direct access to the building.

I had to get a root canal retreatment on 01/29/21 of my front upper right tooth (also known as the #8 tooth).  In addition, I had developed an infection above the tooth that needed to be cleaned out as well.  It had been over 30 years since my last root canal and had to be completely redone.  Dr. Lee was very patient and thorough in discussing all of the 3 options as to how to accomplish this.  And while the option I chose meant that the whole process would overall take longer than I would have hoped, it also provided me with the best chance of success in getting it fixed right in one shot rather than repeated procedures.

With any dental surgery there is always the fear of pain, and especially how much one might experience.  During the procedure I did not experience any pain aside from the 2 stings of when he injected the Novocain which is to be expected.  In less than an hour, he had completed the procedure including the cleaning out of the infection.  As I was checking out, he even provided Ibuprophen to help with the swelling and pain that eventually did come after the Novocain wore off.  However, I was already prepared for this since I knew he had had to go deeper to clear out all of the infection.  The pain throughout the weekend was easily managed by Ibuprophen, and as I write this 3 days later, I am back to normal.

I truly appreciated Dr. Lee and his staff for all of their help in fixing my tooth and highly recommend them if you are in need of an excellent Endodontist!</Review>

Costumer service is bad. Today I went to get some seeds for my little sister's school project and when I got to the register she rolled her eyes when I asked if they were really 4 for 1. Then when I was going to pay I realized I had forgoten to go to the bank to exchange the rolls of pennies and quarters, so I tried to pay with that but she kindly said it was against store policy to take rolls. Yeah I understood that so my aunt dug through her bag to see if she had any money we pooled together like 11 dollars in cash and like 6 dollars in quarters. At this point I noticed she was getting annoyed so I tried to hurry it up. Then when we handed her the money she scuffed and rolled her eyes at the fact that she had to count 24 coins. Like seriously, counting money is part of your job so do it, plus MONEY IS MONEY. Im pretty sure the store owner wouldn't mind a customers paying with change. Honestly this experience has ruin dollar tree for me my aunt was so upset I had to drive. Holly the cashier if you're reading this I hope you have a good day cause if you get upset about customers paying with change than every day must be a long day for you.<//Review>

<Name>Herk Driver< /Name><Date>1621866668042<//Date><Rate>5< /Rate><review>After a nail unexpectedly pierced our tire, DeYoung's came to the rescue.  Mike assured me the team would examine the tire damage for reparability and get us on our way again.  As it turned out, our tire could be patched and Josh expertly handled the repair.  DeYoung's swift and professional diagnosis no doubt saved us hundreds in unnecessary tire replacement and allowed us to continue our summer road trip without delay. < review>
I am now a customer for life! I originally found DeYoung's Automotive after my previous mechanic could not figure out a stalling issue that I was having on my older truck. I dropped off my truck at DeYoung's and they had it diagnosed within the day and fixed the following day. I have since gone back for an oil change (no up-selling which was nice) and most recently an alternator problem. I had my truck towed in midday to find out that they were quite busy. But they went out of their way to squeeze me in and get the job done within a couple hours while I waited. Good thing because I needed my truck the following day for a trip to Big Bear.
I have had nothing but great experiences with the office staff and mechanics. Everyone is professional, friendly, and always upfront about the price of my repairs.
And what I really like to see at my repair shop is a variety of vehicles they work on. The last time I was there they were working on old classic cars, new modern cars, and everything in between. It seems like they work on just about anything. The times I have been there I saw repairs being performed on work trucks, motor homes, motorcycles, and even a battery installation on a boat.
Even though DeYoung's Automotive seems to be busy when I'm there, I always feel like I am their priority. They get me in and out in a very reasonable time. I would give them 10 Stars if I could.
Thank you everybody at DeYoung's Automotive. You all are a lifesaver when it comes to my truck!!!
P.S. I just got my DMV registration in the mail and it says I'm due for a smog inspection, so I'll be back in a couple months.</review>

<Review>My sister and I had the most incredible time at Susie Q Ranch during the weekend of October 10th!
First, the entire staff is truly incredible. Susie Q herself met us at our car to say hello and get our paperwork locked in. We had arrived nearly 30-minutes early to our ride (the first one of the day) and so we were allowed to help brush down some of the horses. I can't begin to describe to you how joyous that was. For two people who have ached for the presence of a horse we were over the moon getting to help prepare these horses for their ride.

Second, the attention to detail was deeply appreciated. My sister and I are experienced riders and we wanted to go on a private 90-minute ride that would allow us to really ride again. Susie assigned us two horses with great personalities and our trail lead was great to offer plenty of opportunities on the trail to get up to a trot and gallop! We were in heaven truly!

Third, the team was kind and let us hang around the ranch after to feed our horses some carrots and spend time with the other animals.

Cannot recommend this ranch enough for any horse back riding adventure you may be looking for! You're supporting a wonderful ranch and a great staff by choosing Susie Q Ranch!<//Review><Date>1602519426286< /Date>< username>

<Review>After reading all of the great reviews online, I was really excited to go here. I took my little sister here for her birthday, and we were surprisingly disappointed. I really, really wanted to like it here...

No one including staff and guests were wearing a mask. While we were outside and distanced, I asked if my sister and I were able to take off our masks and she said ‚Äúno... because one of us had to...‚Äù I was confused because no one else was wearing a mask. I wondered why just us? There are other guests around. Was it because we were both... Asian? I became uncomfortable but brushed it off.

It was only my sister and I in the tour group for the 90 min ride and it was our first time ever riding a horse. Our tour guide didn‚Äôt introduce herself, didn‚Äôt talk to us the whole ride, and didn‚Äôt explain anything about horses or the environment. She rarely checked up on us, and at the end of the tour, didn‚Äôt say goodbye and just left. Another lady who I assume is the owner came to take a photo of us, helped us get off the horses, and that was that. No other comments or even a good bye.

I was confused because all of the reviews said that the staff were friendly and informative... I thought maybe I missed something or if this was how horseback riding is supposed to be... In a time of a pandemic combined with the recent stigmas against Asian communities, I wondered if we were being treated this way because of our race even though we were born and raised in Orange County. It did not feel like a tour, because no one talked to us or even treated us with respect. Regardless, I did not feel welcomed. The horses themselves were well trained and wonderful, but the overall experience was a little jarring. I was confused because I had never experienced anything like this from anyone before, maybe because I am usually with other white folks... It was really disappointing, but had to share my experience to hopefully create change in the way they treat their future visitors.</Review><Pictures>None< /Pictures><resp>{'time': 1615370300366, 'text': 'I am sorry . <Text>$6 wash.
A six dollar wash, through a very thorough machine scrubbing compilation, to be exact.

It won't take off all the hard, sun pressed yellow bird poop stains, leaf sap, or mildews but that's what detailing is for. It's still a self serve style but without you washing your car.

This is better than a self serve by a long shot, and it's only $1 to $2 more (Express).
This includes a full car body air dry (a great one) no matter what wash option, along with free self serve vacuuming at any 20+ park stations within the lot.
This place gives me more time to detail my car rather than spending it on drying.
Almost all the park spots have canopies and keep you shaded from the son.
---
As a side note -- I visit weekly and because so, my washes get upgraded to higher tiers...I think by glitch. I've had five in the span of a year.
---
Thanks Wish Washy! Long time lover.<//Text>< GmapID>

Escape room (detention): quite simple to solve, just the 1st lock is a bit tricky. Maybe thematic, but room decor is quite simple, no hidden rooms and very few (if any) fun props; mostly a series of combination locks with puzzles. Host doesn't monitor your progress (no cameras are set up), but you get a walkie-talkie. There are no usual warnings/explanations about not forcing stuff open, clues below eye level, etc.</review>

< Text>
Chaos Central STAY AWAY
I have been to multiple parties at Laser Quest. My twins wanted a party there, so we decided to throw it there.
It was the worst experience for us and our guests, and sadly some of the guests felt so overwhelmed that they even left without spending any time. This is why?
1. Starting when we took the package we were not informed well about the differences in the party packages and the reasons we should pick one over the other. We should have picked a party with a host. The place is a MAD house, the acoustics of the site is BAD when they are making announcements you cannot hear.
2. When we got to the venue, no one knew what is happening? We did not have a place to keep our gifts, or food or stuff, it was weird to attend the guest and organize a locker and put our things in the fridge and figure out when people should come to get their kids and figure out what needs to be done with the kids or who is a kid in our party or not.
3. When we finally got a party room, it was so cramped. We were told that we would have a bigger party room as we were celebrating two kids it was super narrow room, with the hostess not showing up or serving or helping out.
4. They did not even spell our kid's name right!!
5. Lastly, there were closets in the room, and they were unlocked, so we kept our stuff and gifts in there only to know that they had 2 sided door and ultimately our gifts got mixed up with someone else
the hostesses told us we have 5 mins to leave without helping us pack, which increases confusion we could not correctly wish our guests goodbye.
Overall re-living the party through this review is giving me a headache. Save your dollars and find alternative party places. Pump it up is twice as much fun for kids and grown-ups.</Text>

I hate that I like this place.  They have a lot of things I like at good prices.  The atmosphere is pleasant and the employees are helpful and seem happy.  They also are open till 9:00 (previously till 10:00).

However, I gladly would pay a little more to patronize a local business that's not a foreign-owned chain.  To that end, I like to shop at Farmer Joe's, The Food Mill, House of Produce (a Cambodian grocery store in the Laurel district), and the Berkeley Bowl.  Nonetheless, I often wind up still going to TJ's for the convenience.</review>

< Review>
So it's a pretty standard trader Joe's inside, if you've been to one you've pretty much been to them all. I will say the layout of this one is a bit less optimal than some others.
That said this is one of the busiest locations in the area, if you go during peak hours you will regret it. Parking is also an unmitigated disaster. < review>
Have been a TJ shopper literally across the country for over a decade.   It seems everytime that I take a break and return their offerings are less and less and the prices increase more and more.  This store looked like it had been raided as the shelves aside from the liquor and booze aisles were extremely barren and they were "out" of basic items like LENTILS.  Seriously?!?!  Most of the fresh fruit and juice prices are highway robbery.  TJs used to be about offering healthy inexpensive produce and options, but they seem to be about profit profit profit and as few options for the customer as possible.  Maybe they should just become a Liquor and frozen foodstore as that seems to be their focus,  at least from the looks of this store.  Extremely disappointing.< /review>

<userid>104987415908644159892</userid><username>Anapanasati ‡•ê<//username><time>1558324250473<//time>< rate>
3<//rate>
< Review>
Let me start by saying that I usually like going to this TJ's. It's got a great setup for checkout only two lines to choose - one is for hand-basket folks only, and usually feeds 2-4 registers. The other line is mostly for people with shopping carts (but open to everyone) and feeds all the other registers. No need to try to guess which line is quickest, just queue up.

That being said, on a Sunday evening, most of the store is completely picked over and not restocked. They were out of at least three items today, that I usually get there, and it just makes for a wasted trip. One other caveat: the berry section has really gone downhill. No organic strawberries for a long time now, and the last batch of raspberries molded in just one day. That's a quality issue that they need to sort out.

Aside from that, the options are usually good, along with the prices, but FFS, just keep everything stocked.<//Review>

<Rating>4< /Rating>< Text>
Single line for checkout works very well: moves fast, no choosing a line and then getting stuck behind somebody who is having problems, etc. Even line that winds all the way around store is fast moving and managers help at that point.
Service generally very helpful and return policy excellent.
Parking on roof always available when I need it.
Way better than other supermarkets for my needs.</Text>

<user>115104848618478614014<//user><username>Donald Macleay</username><Date>1515862468740<//Date><rating>3< /rating>< Text>
What do you say about a Trader Joe's?
This one has decent parking in a difficult parking shopping area.  They do have a single line for checkouts, which is a blessing, and another single line for clients with only baskets.  Getting in and out is painless.

Why only 3 stars?  Normal TJ's problems.  So-so produce, (very) rude fellow customers, stocking staff that treats the customers as if we are annoyingly in their way. The mad rush, etc.< /Text>

It's often too crowded and has a thoughtless floor design.

Update 10/12/19:  they've recently revised the floor plan, moved cold case items into a new cold case at the rear of the store, making the shopping experience more spacious and "logical". 0x808f874191610697:0xd7eecd61759ad680< /Gmap_id>
< review>
I have many nice things to say about Trader Joe's in general, and about this particular location specifically.

It's the thin-and-long store layout, with windows at the front, which lends a bit of a darker feel than the Emeryville or Alameda locations. It's not a terrible thing: the thinner store makes it seem like I have to take less steps to get my shopping done.

Trader Joe's is very keto-friendly. My favorites are their meat selections, from the sirloin steak to the grass-fed zero-carb hot dogs, the truffle pate, and the Volpi sopressata salami. There's also the riced cauliflower, grilled artichoke hearts, their coffee selection, and the coconut coffee creamer.

This location is well-stocked, well-managed, with a lot of registers and a good flow.<//review>

<Time>1457456325612</Time><pictures>None</pictures>< text>
If this store, had better parking facilities, more store space, it would be one of the best Trader Joe's in
Northern California.  That being said, it still does not take away from the shopping experience. The
staff is one of the best, most friendly, any company could hope to have. Efficiency and speed, matter
but, at the end of the day, it is how one as a customer is treated, is what counts the most at least,
in my opinion. A customer, should always leave a store, feeling better then when they went in.
I don't live too close to this store but, once in a while I do shop there. The last time, I was in the store
was two days ago. It was busy but was not too busy, to enjoy shopping. (irony to this, for a store to do well, it needs to be busy, to be successful). At any rate, I met two employees that just made my evening. Any company, would be lucky to have them. Unfortunately, even though
I asked for her name, I have forgotten it (to my dismay). She was amazing. Her name, may be Linda,
She would remember me, I think. She actually approached me in the bread department, to ask if I needed help (I must have looked, as if I needed it). She was just great, She recommended a dessert
(zucchini bread) that was terrific. The other employee I want to mention, is Tevin. Tevin, was fast,
upbeat (clearly loves his job) and courteous. I did leave the store, feeling better then when I walked in.
What shopping experience, could beat that. Before concluding, store well supplied and stocked well.
Trader Joe's at Lakeshore Ave, Oakland, is carrying the high standards, that first made it so well known and popular.</text>
